13. Re1
{ White removes the rook from f1 and this allows the bishop on d3 to move. The rook from e1 also prepares the e4-push. }
13... Qb7 { Black plays the usual move. The point is that after } 14. Bc2 Bc4
{ Even though he didn't exchange the light-squared bishops, his own light-squared bishop is very active. From c4, it anticipates White's plan of e4 because after the exchange on e4, ...dxe4, the bishop will find a wonderful spot on the liberated d5-square. }
