{ This is the most commonly played move. White accepts to lose a tempo as he needs to connect his rooks. }
12... Bxd3
{ Black naturally wins the tempo by forcing the queen to move again. } 13. Qxd3
Qb7 { The usual move. Black prepares for the doubling on the a-file. } 14. Qc2
Ra6 { Black now starts the doubling on the a-file. } 15. Rab1
{ White abandons the a-file, so Black first opens it and then controls it by doubling the rooks. }
15... axb4 16. axb4 Rfa8
{ With absolute control over the a-file and comfortable piece development, Black is perfectly fine. The only thing he needs to be careful about is the b5-push, so he can play ...b5 next himself. }
