4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5
{ The fact that Black has several good options for how to deal with the mainline options in the QGD has caused a significant decrease in its popularity. }
5... h6 6. Bxf6 Bxf6 7. Qc2 { An aggressive idea, planning to castle long. }
7... dxc4
{ @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp2pp1/4pb1p/3p4/2PP4/2N2N2/PP2PPPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@ Similarly to the line  7.Qd2  dxc4  Black takes the pawn and starts immediate play in the centre. He will then continue with ...c5. Now the pawn on d4 hangs, so White needs to do something about it. }
8. Ne4
{ The natural move   8.e3  will transpose after  8...c5  9.dxc5  O-O  (@@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp2pp1/4pb1p/3p4/2PP4/2N2N2/PP2PPPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@)  to the line starting with   7.e3  O-O  8.Qc2  c5  9.dxc5  dxc4 }
8... Be7
{ This is the simplest, keeping the bishop pair. Black now wants to defend the pawn on c4 by ...b5, so White must take the pawn. }
9. Qxc4 b6
{ Black plans to develop the bishop on the long diagonal, chase away the knight from e4 and push ...c5. }
