{ Even though this allows White to take on c4 in one go, it is important to start counterplay with ...c5 as soon as possible. The reaction is the same as in the7.Qd2 line. }
9. Bxc4 Nd7
{ This was an important idea by Portisch at the time. Black wants to push ...c5. }
