[White "Chapter 1: The Exchange Variation"]
[Black "White Plays 4.Qc2 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7
{ The point of developing the bishop first is to avoid the development of White's knight to  e2  in the Exchange Variation. This would happen in case of  3...Nf6  4.cxd5  exd5  5.Bg5  Be7  6.e3  c6  7.Bd3  followed by 8. Nge2. This invention by Mikhail Botvinnik is still considered the most promising for White in the Exchange Variation. The idea is not to block the f-pawn so as to be able to build a big center by playing f3 and e4 and later this can develop into a strong kingside attack. With the move order 3...Be7, if White still wants to play the Exchange Variation he will have to make some concessions. }
4. Qc2
{ This is a tricky attempt to enter the Exchange Variation by keeping the knight on g1. }
4... Nf6 { Black develops normally. } 5. Bg5
{ White still keeps the knight on g1 and hopes to transpose to an Exchange Variation, but this is impossible if Black recaptures on d5 with a knight. }
5... h6 { Black plays in the same manner as in the Main Line with 5.Bg5. } 6.
Bh4
{ In case of   6.Bxf6  Bxf6  7.e3  O-O  White has nothing better than play  8.Nf3  transposing to the chapter,  'The Main Line: 5. Bg5 h6 6.Bxf6', }
6... O-O 7. e3 { Still keeping the knight on g1 and setting a small trap. }
7... c5
{ Black is careful and doesn't fall into the trap, which occurs in the natural move   7...Nbd7  when  8.cxd5  would force a favourable Exchange Variation for White because Black cannot recapture on  d5  with a knight:  8...Nxd5  9.Nxd5  Bxh4  10.Nxc7  wins a pawn for White. }
8. dxc5
{ Taking on d5 is bad for White as   8.cxd5  is met by  8...cxd4  9.exd4  Nxd5  when White has nothing to show for the weak IQP. }
8... dxc4
{ This is the simplest, releasing the tension in the centre and then recapturing the pawn on c5 with the queen. }
9. Bxc4 Qa5 10. Nf3 Qxc5 11. Be2 Nc6
{ With easy play for Black who will finish development with ...Bd7, ...Rfd8 and ...Rac8. Then if he needs to open the d-file, the bishop from d7 will drop back to e8. }
