Bf5 12. Ne2 { The knight goes to c3. } 12... Nd7
{ Black finished development and now we have a complex middlegame ahead. One general idea for Black is that he should castle on the same side as White because it will avoid an attack against his king. }
13. O-O-O g5
{ Since White determined the position of his king, this means that Black will also castle long. Black takes the opportunity to gain space on the kingside and liberate the g6-square for his bishop to remain on the b1-h7 diagonal. }
14. Bh2 Bg6
{ The bishop is better here than on e6. From g6, it is more active and it controls the e4-square. }
15. Nc3 Nb6
{ Liberating the d7-square for the queen so that Black can castle long. It also allows for the exchange of the dark-squared bishops after ...Bd6. Black is quite comfortable here with his pieces on good squares. }
