11. Nge2
{ With this development, White plans to have the f3-move at his disposal with the aim to aid g4 and/or e4. }
11... Nf6
{ A natural move allowing the light-squared bishop to enter the game. } 12. f3
{ White controls e4 and g4. } 12... Be6
{ Black's plan is to develop the queen and castle long. Note that White doesn't really threaten to obtain a full center with e4 as after ... dxe4, fxe4, the g4-square would be a good spot for the knight from where it will target f2 and e3. }
13. Nf4
{ In case of   13.O-O-O  the Black queen can go to c7  13...Qc7  followed by ...O-O-O. }
13... Qd6
{ Defending the bishop on e6 since White threatened to take on e6 and then after ...fxe6 to take on g6, for example:   13...Qc7  14.Nxe6  fxe6  15.Bxg6 }
14. Na4
{ After   14.O-O-O  O-O-O  Black is very comfortable. He can continue with ...Kb8 to liberate the c8-square for the rook or the bishop. }
14... Bd7
{ Removing the bishop from e6 so the queen can drop back to c7 to defend the b7-pawn. }
15. Nc5 Qc7 { With ideas like ...O-O-O and ... Bd6, Black has very good play. }
