1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5
{ The fact that Black has several good options for how to deal with the mainline options in the QGD has caused a significant decrease in its popularity. }
5... h6
{ Black immediately chases away the bishop and makes a useful move - the luft for the king, if he castles short, will always be useful. }
6. Bh4 O-O
{ Black finished with the development of the kingside and now White needs to decide how to proceed. }
7. e3 { This is by far the main move, but there are alternatives. } 7... Nbd7
{ This has been used by Kramnik and he had excellent results with it. This move, together with the fact that the alternatives like the Lasker Variation with   7...Ne4  and the Tartakower Variation with   7...b6  are perfectly viable, are the main reasons why the move 5.Bg5 dropped in popularity and is less seen nowadays. }
8. Qc2 c5 { Attacking White's center in the usual manner. } 9. Rd1 Qa5
{ Pinning the knight on c3 and activating the queen. } 10. cxd5
{ The move   10.Bd3  is harmless. Black can employ the typical reaction when the bishop moves to d3 - to take on c4 to gain tempo for further development:  10...dxc4  11.Bxc4  a6  followed by ...b5, ...Bb7 with easy play. }
10... Nxd5
{ Black takes with a knight and exchanges the dark-squared bishops. } 11. Bxe7
{ Retreating only helps Black, after   11.Bg3  Nxc3  12.bxc3  Nf6  followed by ...Nd5. White's queenside is under attack. }
11... Nxe7 12. Be2
{ Taking on c5 isn't better,   12.dxc5  Qxc5  and the knight on c3 is pinned because the queen on c2 is unprotected. Black will continue with ...b6, ...Nf6 and ...Bb7. }
12... Nf6 { Liberating the d7-square for the undeveloped bishop. } 13. O-O cxd4
14. Rxd4 { After   14.Nxd4  Bd7  Black finishes development without problems. }
14... Bd7 { Black is in time to get the bishop to c6. } 15. Rfd1
{ If   15.Ne4  then  15...Nfd5  when the knight closes the d-file. Black can proceed with ...Bc6 and putting the rooks in the centre. }
15... Bc6
{ Black will place a rook on c8 and most probably a knight on d5 to close the d-file. }
