{ Luring a White piece on c4 in order to proceed with ...a6 and ...b5, creating activity on the queenside and helping the development of the light-squared bishop. There is no danger along the d-file since the queen can easily go to c7, b6 or a5 if necessary. }
11. Bxc4 a6
{ And it's easier for Black to create something on the queenside than for White on the kingside. Black's play rolls with ...b5, ... Bb7, ...Rc8, etc. }
