7. e3 { This is by far the main move, but there are alternatives. } 7... Nbd7
{ This has been used by Kramnik and he had excellent results with it. This move, together with the fact that the alternatives like the Lasker Variation with   7...Ne4  and the Tartakower Variation with   7...b6  are perfectly viable, are the main reasons why the move 5.Bg5 dropped in popularity and is less seen nowadays. }
8. Rc1
{ The exchange on d5 should be met by the thematic   8.cxd5  Nxd5  avoiding a favorable Exchange Variation for White after   8...exd5  9.Bd3 }
8... c5
{ This thematic push ensures Black gets an equal game. Despite this, the whole line became popular only after Kramnik took it up and achieved excellent results in the second half of the 2010s. }
9. dxc5 dxc4
{ Striving to clarify the position in the center by symmetrically taking on the c-file. }
