{ Taking with knight is met by   13.Nxd4  a6  and in view of the threat of ...e5, White must take on d7,  14.Bxd7  Bxd7  with easy play for Black who has the bishop pair. }
13... Qb6 { Forcing the exchange of queens. } 14. Qxb6 Nxb6
{ Now Black wants to develop the bishop to d7. } 15. Rfd1
{ This is the most natural move, but after } 15... Rd8
{ With the idea of ...Bd7, Black solves his problems. } 16. Rxd8+ Bxd8 17. Rd1
Be7
{ Black's position is rock solid. He will play ...a6 and/or ...Nd5 and develop the bishop to d7 with an equal endgame. }
