[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Chapter 4: The Main Line: 5.Bf4"]
[Black "Main Line 7.Qc2"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3
{ White usually develops both knights before developing the bishop to f4. }
4... Nf6 5. Bf4 O-O
{ Black played the usual moves and finished the development of the kingside. }
6. e3
{ @@StartFEN@@rnbqk1nr/ppp1bppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/2N5/PP2PPPP/R1BQKBNR w KQkq - 2 4@@EndFEN@@  The most common move. The other moves transpose to the lines after   4.Bf4  Nf6  5.e3  O-O }
6... Nbd7
{ With this move, Black wants to to play ...c5 and take on c5 with the knight. }
7. Qc2 c5 8. Rd1
{ After   8.dxc5  Nxc5  (@@StartFEN@@rnbqk1nr/ppp1bppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/2N5/PP2PPPP/R1BQKBNR w KQkq - 2 4@@EndFEN@@)  we have a transposition to the line starting with   4.Bf4  Nf6  5.e3  O-O  6.Qc2  c5  7.dxc5  Na6  8.Nf3  Nxc5  while after   8.cxd5  Nxd5  9.Nxd5  exd5  10.Bd3  we transpose to the line 7. cxd5 Nxd5 8. Nxd5 exd5 9. Bd3 c5 10. Qc2 }
8... cxd4 { Luring the rook to d4. } 9. Rxd4
{ Taking with pawn gives Black a good version of the IQP after   9.exd4  dxc4  10.Bxc4  Nb6  with excellent control over the d5-square and quick development of the bishop with ...Bd7-c6.  Taking with knight loses a piece after   9.Nxd4?  e5 }
9... Qa5 { Pinning the knight and removing the queen from the d-file. } 10. Bg3
{ The bishop moves away from possible attacks after   10.cxd5  Nxd5 } 10... Nb6
{ Attacking White's pawn on c4. } 11. Nd2
{ White defends the pawn and breaks the pin on the c3-knight. } 11... dxc4
{ Black releases the tension in the center and exchanges one pair of minor pieces in order to gain time for the development of the light-squared bishop. }
12. Bxc4
{ White wants to have an active knight on c4. After   12.Nxc4  Nxc4  13.Bxc4  Bd7  Black easily finishes development. }
12... Nxc4
{ Black now has the bishop pair but still needs to develop the light-squared bishop. }
13. Nxc4 Qa6 { The queen is out of harm's way on a6. } 14. O-O Rd8
{ Challenging White's dominance on the d-file. } 15. Rxd8+
{ After   15.Rfd1  Rxd4  16.Rxd4  Bd7  Black finishes development. } 15... Bxd8
16. Ne5 Bd7
{ Black doesn't mind the loss of the bishop pair as he finishes development. }
17. Nxd7 Nxd7 18. Rd1 Nf6 { With an equal position. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
