[White "Chapter 4: The Main Line: 5.Bf4"]
[Black "Main Line 7.Be2 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3
{ White usually develops both knights before developing the bishop to f4. }
4... Nf6 5. Bf4 O-O
{ Black played the usual moves and finished the development of the kingside. }
6. e3
{ @@StartFEN@@rnbqk1nr/ppp1bppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/2N5/PP2PPPP/R1BQKBNR w KQkq - 2 4@@EndFEN@@  The most common move. The other moves transpose to the lines after   4.Bf4  Nf6  5.e3  O-O }
6... Nbd7
{ With this move, Black wants to to play ...c5 and take on c5 with the knight. }
7. Be2
{ White develops and wants to castle as soon as possible. Note that after   7.Bd3  dxc4  8.Bxc4  we have a transposition to the line   7.Be2  dxc4  8.Bxc4 }
7... dxc4 8. O-O
{ After   8.Bxc4  c5  9.dxc5  Nxc5  10.O-O  (@@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pppnbppp/4pn2/8/2pP1B2/2N1PN2/PP2BPPP/R2QK2R w KQ - 0 8@@EndFEN@@)  we have a transposition to the line   8.O-O  c5  9.dxc5  Nxc5  10.Bxc4  while after   8.Bxc4  c5  9.O-O  cxd4  we transpose to   8.O-O  c5  9.Bxc4 }
8... c5 9. Bxc4 cxd4
{ Black takes in this moment so White cannot recapture with a knight in view of the fork after ...e5. }
10. Qxd4
{ Black has good play against the IQP in case of   10.exd4  Nb6  followed by ...Nbd5 and ...Bd7-c6. }
10... Nb6
{ A multi-purpose move, liberating the d7-square for the light-squared bishop, threatening to take on c4 and offering an exchange of queens. }
11. Be2
{ After the exchange of queens, White wants to place the bishop on f3 to put pressure on Black's queenside. }
11... Qxd4
{ The endgame is alright for Black, though he still needs to finish development. }
12. Nxd4 Nbd5 { Forcing an exchange of one pair of knights. } 13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14.
Bg3 Bd7
{ Black finished development and stands well. The possible endgame with an IQP after }
15. Bf3 Rfd8 { With the idea of ...Be8. } 16. Bxd5 exd5
{ This endgame is fine for Black because the pair of bishops compensates for the IQP. Since White has a dark-squared bishop, he can never threaten the pawn on d5, which means that Black is safe. }
