11. Qb1
{ The queen is behind the b-pawn now and this makes the b5-push stronger, so Black should be a bit careful. }
11... Bb7
{ Again following the rule of thumb works - the bishop is still on f1 so Black prepares ...Ba6 by playing ...Bb7 and ...Qc8 first. }
12. Bd3 Qc8 13. O-O Ba6 { Achieving the aim. } 14. Bxa6
