15. Rc1
{ Now   15.b5  can be met by  15...Qb7  when Black controls well his queenside and the exchange of the b and c-pawns will give him free play there. }
15... Qb7
{ Moving away from possible b5-ideas and preparing the usual plan of doubling on the a-file or of taking on b4 followed by an exchange on a1. A sample line is }
16. Rc2 axb4 17. axb4 Rxa1 18. Qxa1 Ra8
{ With easy play regardless if White chooses to exchange the remaining pair of rooks or not. }
