Ng5
{ This is the difference with the analogous line after 8.h3 - without a pawn on h6. White can play this move active move, seeking to exchange the knight on e4 from g5 rather than d2. }
17... Ndf6
{ Black supports the knight on e4. Here   17...Nc3?!  isn't very good as after  18.Nxc3  bxc3  19.Rxc3  White has attacking possibilities after h4 and Qd3 or Qg4, all thanks to the knight on g5. }
18. Nxe4
{ This was played by Anand in his only win in the two matches against Carlsen. }
18... dxe4
