19. Nd6
{ White forces play. After   19.Qc2  Nd5  20.O-O  b3  21.Qc6  h6  we have a transposition to the lines after 18.Qc2. }
19... Bxd6 20. Bxd6 b3
{ This is the main source of Black's counterplay in the sharp lines after 11.Bxa6. His powerful and well-advanced pawn@@StartBracket@@s@@EndBracket@@ on the queenside allow him to sacrifice material and still have excellent compensation. }
21. Bxf8 Kxf8
{ The position is very sharp but Black has excellent chances. If he manages to take the c7-pawn without concessions, he will simply be winning because of the strong pawn on b3. He wants to play ...Nd5 and ...Ra7 rounding up the c7-pawn, so White needs to seek active play. }
