Rac8
{ Black is willing to sacrifice material in order to simplify the position and start to use his own passed pawn. With the c7-pawn safely blockaded and the untouchable knight on d5, he doesn't run any risks. }
27. Nxc8 Rxc8
{ The position remains dynamically balanced, but with Black having a clear plan of ...b5-b4, it is White who is under pressure to find counterplay here. }
