1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. g4
{ Tried by Daniil Dubov against Radjabov at the Airthings Masters, played in January 2021. }
5... O-O { After castling, Black is ready to play in the center. } 6. g5 Ne4
{ The knight targets both the knight on c3 and the pawn on g5. } 7. Bg2
{ Dubov's improvement over  7.Qc2  which is most easily met by  7...Nxc3  8.Qxc3  a5  (threatening ...Bb4)   9.Bd2  Bb4  and after the exchange of bishops, White won't be able to defend both the pawn on g5 and the pawn on c4. If he takes on d2, the pawn on g5 will fall; if he takes with the queen, the pawn on c4 falls. }
7... Nxc3
{ This is simpler than Radjabov's  7...c5  which also gave Black good play in the aforementioned game. }
8. bxc3 Nd7
{ The knight is headed for b6 from where it will target the weakened c4-square. }
9. cxd5 exd5 10. h4 Nb6
{ Black has an easy game based on the light squares. His ideas are ...Nc4, ...Bf5, and possibly the undermining move ...f6. }
