Bd6 { Putting even more pressure on e5. } 10. Nxd7 Qxd7
{ The endgame is quite comfortable for Black, who has good development and no weaknesses. }
11. Qxd7 Nxd7 12. cxd5 Bxd5
{ Black would like to exchange the fianchettoed bishop on g2 before taking with a pawn on d5. }
13. e4 { White occupies the center. } 13... Bb7
{ Black's position is compact and he will attack the center by ...c5. } 14. Rd1
{ White anticipates ...c5 and envisions play on the d-file after dxc5 and Nc4. }
14... Be7 { Therefore, Black needs to prepare the ...c5 push. } 15. Nc4 Nf6
{ Removing the knight from the vulnerable spot on the d-file and attacking the e4-pawn. After }
16. f3 c5 { Black equalizes, having executed the liberating push ...c5. } *

