12... Qe7 { Liberating the 8th rank for the rooks. } 13. Bxc4 Rfd8
{ Since Black has a queenside majority, he leaves the queenside rook to support a possible pawn advance. }
14. Qc2 Nd4
{ Black's activity is quite apparent, he wins a tempo with every move he plays. }
15. Qd3 a5
{ Black wants to advance his queenside pawns. His excellent pieces and the activity he has more than compensate for White's bishop pair. }
