14. Bxe4 Qc7
{ Defending the bishop on b7 so as to allow ...c5, and at the same time attacking the pawn on e5. }
15. Bc3 c5
{ The position is equal. Black will be the first one to put a rook on the open d-file, meaning that he has little to worry about. }
