{ Black initiaties a simplifying sequence that makes it easier for him to play. He temporarily wins a pawn after }
14. Bxb4 Bxc4 15. Nxc4 dxc4 { But after } 16. Bxe7 Qxe7 17. Nd2
{ White will regain it. Still, removing the knight from f3 allows } 17... e5
{ Which gives Black problem-free position, with all his pieces well-placed and no weaknesses. }
