16. Ne5
{ After   16.Na4  b5  17.Nc5  Nxc5  18.dxc5  Rc8  Black is very solid and without problems as the c-pawn is under attack and not going anywhere. }
16... Nxe5 { Exchanging the centralized knight. } 17. Bxe5
{ If   17.dxe5  Nd7  defends the pawn on b6. } 17... b5
{ Grabbing some queenside space and avoiding   17...Nd7  18.Bc7  with some initiative for White. }
18. a4 Bc6
{ Defending the pawn as White cannot take it twice in view of the pin after ...Qb7 which would cost him a piece. If allowed, Black now wants to play ...Nd7-b6-c4, after taking care of the a4-b5 tension on the queenside. }
