{ Immediately putting pressure on e5, black wants to play ...Qc7 next to attack the centralized knight. }
10. Bg3
{ is rather harmless, leading to simplifications that favor Black after } 10...
Qc7 11. Nxc6
{ This is an attempt to establish a blockade on the dark squares, but it doesn't work. }
11... bxc6 12. Bxd6 Qxd6 13. Qb4
{ Otherwise, Black will castle and play ...c5, when he will be better. } 13...
Ke7
{ The idea to take on b4 and follow it up with ...Rhb8, while if queens are exchanged, the king will be nicely centralized. }
14. Qxd6+ Kxd6 { The king is nicely centralized. } 15. Ba6
{ Preventing ...a5. } 15... Rhb8 16. b4
{ Still hoping to establish a blockade, but after } 16... Rb6 17. Be2 a5
{ White's queenside structure breaks down and this gives Black a solid advantage. }
