Bb7
{ Here White needs to make a principled choice - whether to go for slower play with e3, Qe2 etc. or to take on d5 and engage in central play. The move  8.d4?  is not very good as after  8...dxc4   @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/p1p1bppp/1p2pn2/3p4/2P5/1P3NP1/P2PPPBP/RNBQ1RK1 w - - 0 7@@EndFEN@@ we have a transposition to the line  7.d4  Bb7  8.Bb2  dxc4  9.bxc4  c5 }
