[Black "Blackmar-Diemer Gambit #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6
{ Note that the move  3.Bf4  after  3...c5  4.e3  cxd4  5.exd4  a6  would transpose to the London System,  (@@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3p4/3P4/8/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 2@@EndFEN@@)  As seen in the line  2.Bf4  Nf6  3.e3  c5  4.Nc3  cxd4  5.exd4  a6 }
3. e4 { The Blackmar-Diemer Gambit is unsound in more than one way. } 3... dxe4
4. f3 exf3 5. Qxf3
{ White sacrifices a second pawn, as if having no compensation for the first one wasn't enough. }
5... Qxd4
{ Black should take everything as long as there is nothing concrete to pose any danger. }
6. Be3 Qg4 { Moving away with a tempo. } 7. Qf2 Qf5
{ Again gaining tempo and threatening ...Ng4. } 8. Qd2 e6
{ Black has a safe position and is two pawns up. He will finish development unhindered and castle, which will give him a winning position. }
