3. Bg5
{ The Veresov Attack. It is not very popular nowadays, and the reason is that the main idea of the opening, to push e4, backfires for White in all the lines. In fact, White's best play is to play slowly with Nf3 and e3, but then why put the knight on c3? }
3... c6
{ This is actually a small provocation, as Black can also start with  3...Nbd7  and then most lines probably transpose to the lines we analyze. The point of the provocation is to nudge white to take on f6, which some Veresov players like to do, but then Black has excellent play with a clear plan in mind. Another point of the move is that it opens the a5-d8 diagonal for the queen so she can come to b6 or a5. }
4. f3
{ This is a typical Veresov idea, to build a center by f3 and e4, but it is not very good. This line shows best why the Veresov is not popular. }
