7... Qa5 { Threatening both pawns on e5 and e4. } 8. exf6
{ This wins a pawn, but leaves White with horribly weak dark squares. } 8...
Qxg5 9. fxg7 Bxg7
{ Black has marvelous compensation here. The control over the dark-squares is a plus because he can continue to play on the dark squares, while White's extra pawn gives him nothing. }
