9... Nf6 10. O-O Nbd7 11. c4 O-O
{ Black finished development and has no problems whatsoever. } 12. Nc3 Qa6
{ An interesting move, that somewhat annoys White due to the pin on the c4-pawn and undefended queen on d3. }
13. Rfd1 Rfd8 14. a4 Rac8
{ Black is prepared for anything White may try. He has put the rooks in the center and has a very compact position. He can place the bishop on b4, and can also harass the bishop on g3 by ...Nh5. }
