Nc3
{ White cannot take the pawn since  10.Bxd5  exd5  11.Qxd5  Be6  followed by ...Qxb2 is practically winning for Black. }
10... Nxc3
{ Black doesn't waste time and exchanges on c3 so that he can castle next. }
11. bxc3 O-O
{ Black has excellent play here. His king is safe, and he will finish development with ...Qc7, ...b6, ...Bb7, and ...Nd7 or ...Nc6-a5, and will then target the central pair of pawns on c3 and d4 and the weak square on c4. }
