1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3
{ This is the starting move for the Colle and Zukertort systems. Note that the move  3.g3  e6  would transpose to the chapter on theReti Opening   and the move  3.Bf4  would lead us to theLondon System. }
3... c5 4. dxc5
{ The move   4.c3  (@@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp1pppp/5n2/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 2 3@@EndFEN@@)  is analyzed after the   3.c3  c5  4.e3  move-order. }
4... e6 { Black simply wants to recapture on c5. } 5. c4
{ Note that  5.b4  a5  6.c3  b6  (@@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp1pppp/5n2/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 2 3@@EndFEN@@)  transposes to the line analysed after   3.c3  c5  4.dxc5  a5  5.e3  e6  6.b4  b6 }
5... Bxc5 6. Nbd2
{ With the knight on d2, White wants to play b3 and Bb2@@StartBracket@@ or a3, b4 and Bb2@@EndBracket@@, but Black is still very quick with ...d4. }
6... O-O 7. a3 a5 { Preventing b4. } 8. Bd3
