{ This is an attempt to play a Queen's Gambit Accepted with colors reversed.  The capture on d5 is met by   7.cxd5  Nxd5  with ...b6 and ...Bb7 to follow next,  while the move   7.Nbd2  is met by the typical  7...b6  followed by ...Bb7 and ...Nbd7. The thing to remember is that whenever White takes on d5, Black should recapture with a piece.  In case of   7.Nc3  cxd4  we have a transposition to the chapter  The Main Line Various  (@@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@)  The line   1.d4  d5  2.c4  e6  3.Nc3  Be7  4.Nf3  Nf6  5.e3  O-O  6.b3  c5  7.Bb2  cxd4 }
