9... Bb7 10. Ne4 Nxe4
{ The exchanges in the center simplify the position and indicate that White must abandon any hope of kingside threats. }
11. Bxe4 Bxe4 12. Qxe4 Nd7
{ Defending the rook on a8 and planning ...c5 next. } 13. O-O c5
{ With ...Nf6 next, and then ... Qb6 @@StartBracket@@or ...Qa5@@EndBracket@@, ...Rac8, and ...Rfd8. Black is comfortable as he has very good central control and space advantage on the queenside. }
