{ This creates quite a few threats, but after } 17. Rxc5
{ White avoids the danger. } 17... Rxc5 18. Qb3
{ White got two pieces for the rook, but Black's initiative still makes it dangerous for White. }
18... Qc6 19. Be3 { White defends well, forcing further simplifications. }
19... Bxe2 20. Bxc5 Bxf3 21. Qxf3 Qxc5 22. O-O b5
{ The position is equal, though Black finds it easier to create a passed pawn on the queenside. }
23. h4 h6 24. Rb1 a6 25. Rb3 Qe5 26. g3 Rd4 27. Re3 a5
{ Black maximized the activity of his pieces and will create a passed pawn with ...b4 next, but then it will be impossible to make further progress. }
28. Qg4 b4 29. axb4 axb4 30. Qc8+ Kh7 31. Qb7
{ White controls the b-pawn and defends the e4-pawn at the same time. } 31...
f6 32. Kg2 Rc4 33. Qd5 { Forcing a drawn rook endgame. } 33... Qxd5 34. exd5
